node.text:
"If we didn't have bees to do pollination, we'd only be eating wheat and rice." 🐝

Research assistant Rui Gonçalves of the Oxford Bee Lab is studying bee nutrition to ensure UK bee populations can grow.

Discover why Rui's role is one of #101Jobs that change the world ⬇️
https://www.ukri.org/our-work/101-jobs-that-change-the-world/

#TruePlanet #Oxford #OxfordUni #OxfordUniversity #Bees #Beekeeping #BeesNeedsWeek

node.title: Beekeeping is in the top 101 jobs that change the world

Today is #DontStepOnABeeDay! 🐝
.

.
Find out more ➡️ oxfordplanbee.web.ox.ac.uk
#Oxford #OxfordUni #OxfordUniversity #bee #bees #trueplanet

NEW: #OxfordVaccine reaches 1,000,000,000 doses released 💉

We're delighted to announce our vaccine has reached a significant milestone of one billion doses.

Oxford- @astrazeneca's joint vision was to make the vaccine available to the world, on a not-for-profit basis for the world during the pandemic, and in perpetuity in low-and middle-income countries.

AstraZeneca have been able to have the vaccine approved and licenced for use in over 170 countries, with these one billion doses being delivered from over 20 manufacturing sites across the world, including the Serum Institute of India.

For more information, please visit: ox.ac.uk/news/
